==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Winters bark
<hw>Win"ter's bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
aromatic bark of tree (<spn>Drimys Winteri</spn> syn. <spn>Drymis
Winteri</spn>) of the Magnolia family, which is found in <geog>Southern
Chile</geog>. It was first used as a cure for scurvy by its discoverer,
<person>Captain John <etsep>Winter</etsep></person>, vice admiral to
<person>sir Francis Drake</person>, in 1577.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wintertide</ent>⟦br⟧
